<http://viaf.org/viaf/33278380/treasure>
    a rdac:C10001 ;
    rdaxd:P00018 "http://viaf.org/viaf/33278380/treasure" ;
    rdawd:P10088 "The world treasury of science fiction" ;
    rdfs:label "The world treasury of science fiction" ;
    abi:P02 abi:T01 ;
    rdawd:P10330 "Includes Vonnegut, Kurt Jr., \"Harrison Bergeron\"/Campbell, John W. Jr., \"Forgetfulness\"/Berryman, John, \"Special Flight\"/Ballard, J. G., \"Chronopolis\"/Tensei, Kono, \"Triceratops\"/Sturgeon, Theodore, \"The Man Who Lost the Sea\"/Armer, Karl Michael, \"On the Inside Track\"/Davidson, Avram, \"The Golem\"/Rebetez-Cortes, Rene, \"The New Prehistory\"/Clarke, Arthur C., \"A Meeting with Medusa\"/Klein, Gerard, \"The Valley of Echoes\"/Wolfe, Gene, \"The Fifth Head of Cerberus\"/Updike, John, \"The Chaste Planet\"/Henneberg, Nathalie-Charles, \"The Blind Pilot\"/Bester, Alfred, \"The Men Who Murdered Mohammed\"/Pairpuppets, \"Manuel van Loggem\"/Kornbluth, C.M., \"Two Dooms\"/Lem, Stanislaw, \"Tale of the Computer that Fought a Dragon\"/Heinlein, Robert A., \"The Green Hills of Earth\"/Sheckley, Robert, \"Ghost V\"/Varley, John, \"The Phantom of Kansas\"/Nesvadba, Josef, \"Captain Nemo's Last Adventure\"/Niven, Larry, \"Inconstant Moon\"/Pohl, Frederik, \"The Gold at the Starbow's End\"/Calvino, Italo, \"A Sign in Space\" \"The Spiral\"/Asimov Isaac, \"The Dead Past\"/van Ewyck, Annemarie, \"The Lens\"/Sturgeon, Theodore, \"The Hurkle Is a Happy Beast\"/Bradbury, Ray, \"Zero Hour\"/Le Guin, Ursula K., \"Nine Lives\"/Burgess, Anthony, \"The Muse\"/Allen, Steve, \"The Public Hating\"/Leiber, Fritz, \"Poor Superman\"/Disch, Thomas M., \"Angouleme\"/Knight, Damon, \"Stranger Station\" and more." .

<http://viaf.org/viaf/43347281/researchdatamanagement>
    a rdac:C10001 ;
    rdaxd:P00018 "http://viaf.org/viaf/43347281/researchdatamanagement" ;
    rdawd:P10088 "Research data management : practical strategies for information professionals" ;
    rdfs:label "Research data management : practical strategies for information professionals (Ray, Joyce M.)" ;
    abi:P02 abi:T01 ;
    rdawd:P10330 "\"It has become increasingly accepted that important digital data must be retained and shared in order to preserve and promote knowledge, advance research in and across all disciplines of scholarly endeavor, and maximize the return on investment of public funds. To meet this challenge, colleges and universities are adding data services to existing infrastructures by drawing on the expertise of information professionals who are already involved in the acquisition, management and preservation of data in their daily jobs. Data services include planning and implementing good data management practices, thereby increasing researchers' ability to compete for grant funding and ensuring that data collections with continuing value are preserved for reuse. This volume provides a framework to guide information professionals in academic libraries, presses, and data centers through the process of managing research data from the planning stages through the life of a grant project and beyond. It illustrates principles of good practice with use-case examples and illuminates promising data service models through case studies of innovative, successful projects and collaborations\"--" ;
    rdawo:P10055 <http://viaf.org/viaf/43347281> ;
    rdawo:P10147 <http://viaf.org/viaf/43347281/researchdatamanagement/chronopolis> .

