    rdaxd:P00029 "parent" ;
    rdaed:P20312 "Culture control critique : allegories of reading the present" ;
    rdfs:label "Culture control critique (Beckman, Frida)" ;
    rdaed:P20071 "Introduction -- Culture, control, critique. Cultural critique from the Frankfurt School until today -- Formalism, allegory, totality. Allegory and representation -- Allegory and the present -- Space, allegory, control. Spatial preoccupations -- Celebrating ruins: The drowned world, The drought, The crystal world -- Filling the gaps: Crash, Concrete island, High rise -- Coming into allegory: Cocaine nights, Super-Cannes, Millennium people, Kingdom come -- Totalities, allegories and revolutions -- Cultural critique and form -- Time, allegory, control. Timely preoccupations -- In and out of time: \"Chronopolis\" and in time -- Cultural critique and form -- Vision, allegory, control. Visual preoccupations -- bread and circuses: The hunger games -- Cultural critique and form -- Conclusion." ;
    rdaeo:P20001 <http://rdaregistry.info/termList/RDAContentType/1020> ;
